body_text.text:
There were marked differences in ILI viral types and peak activities in hospitalized adult (Figure 1
) and paediatric (Figure 2
) patients. Among adults, influenza A cases peaked in February to March. Interestingly, hMPV peak activity occurred inversely relative to peak influenza A activity. There was only one case of influenza B. There were no real sentinel peaks or warnings of impending influenza A activity in adults, although a modest increase in RSV activity was recorded in November and December.
